00:01:16.138 --> 00:01:17.485
Let me show you.

00:01:17.485 --> 00:01:22.640
So this, let's just say whatever angle you have here.

00:01:22.640 --> 00:01:24.590
So this is going to be 90 degrees over here.

00:01:24.590 --> 00:01:27.005
Whatever angle you have over here

00:01:27.005 --> 00:01:27.980
so let's call that theta

00:01:27.980 --> 00:01:30.198
this over here, they have to add up to 180.

00:01:30.198 --> 00:01:33.364
So theta plus 90 plus this has to be 180

00:01:33.364 --> 00:01:36.569
Or theta plus this has to be 90

00:01:36.569 --> 00:01:40.315
or you could just call this 90 minus theta.

00:01:40.315 --> 00:01:43.600
Now, if I were to take the same thing

00:01:43.600 --> 00:01:46.267
if I took another kind of wedge like this

00:01:46.267 --> 00:01:48.252
